#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:11
msgid "Cross compilation"
msgstr "交叉編譯"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:13
msgid ""
"Nixpkgs offers powerful tools to cross-compile software for various system "
"types."
msgstr "Nixpkgs 提供強大的工具，可為各種系統類型交叉編譯軟體。"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:15
msgid "What do you need?"
msgstr "您需要什麼？"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:18
msgid "Experience using C compilers"
msgstr "使用 C 編譯器的經驗"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:19
msgid "Basic knowledge of the [Nix language](<reading-nix-language>)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:21
msgid "Platforms"
msgstr "平臺"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:23
msgid ""
"When compiling code, we can distinguish between the **build platform**, "
"where the executable is *built*, and the **host platform**, where the "
"compiled executable *runs*. [^id3]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:25
msgid ""
"**Native compilation** is the special case where those two platforms are the "
"same. **Cross compilation** is the general case where those two platforms "
"are not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:28
msgid ""
"Cross compilation is needed when the host platform has limited resources "
"(such as CPU) or when it's not easily accessible for development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:30
msgid ""
"The `nixpkgs` package collection has world-class support for cross "
"compilation, after many years of hard work by the Nix community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:36
msgid "What's a target platform?"
msgstr "什麼是目標平臺？"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:38
msgid "There is a third concept for a platform we call a **target platform**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:40
msgid ""
"The target platform is relevant to cases where you want to build a compiler "
"binary. In such cases, you would build a compiler on the *build platform*, "
"run it to compile code on the *host platform*, and run the final executable "
"on the *target platform*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:43
msgid ""
"Since this is rarely needed, we will assume that the target is identical to "
"the host."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:45
msgid "Determining the host platform config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:47
msgid ""
"The build platform is determined automatically by Nix during the configure "
"phase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:49
msgid ""
"The host platform is best determined by running this command on the host "
"platform:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:51
msgid ""
"$ $(nix-build '<nixpkgs>' -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-23.11 -A gnu-config)/"
"config.guess\n"
"aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n"
msgstr ""
"$ $(nix-build '<nixpkgs>' -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-23.11 -A gnu-config)/"
"config.guess\n"
"aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:56
msgid ""
"In case this is not possible (for example, when the host platform is not "
"easily accessible for development), the platform config has to be "
"constructed manually via the following template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:58
msgid "<cpu>-<vendor>-<os>-<abi>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:62
msgid "This string representation is used in `nixpkgs` for historic reasons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:64
msgid ""
"Note that `<vendor>` is often `unknown` and `<abi>` is optional. There's "
"also no unique identifier for a platform, for example `unknown` and `pc` are "
"interchangeable (which is why the script is called `config.guess`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:67
msgid ""
"If you can't install Nix, find a way to run `config.guess` (usually comes "
"with the autoconf package) from the OS you're able to run on the host "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:69
msgid "Some other common examples of platform configs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:71
msgid "aarch64-apple-darwin14"
msgstr "aarch64-apple-darwin14"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:72
