#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:144
msgid "Specifying the host platform"
msgstr "指定主機平臺"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:146
msgid "The mechanism for setting up cross compilation works as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:148
msgid ""
"Take the build platform configuration and apply it to the current package "
"set, called `pkgs` by convention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:150
msgid ""
"The build platform is implied in `pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {}` to be the "
"current system. This produces a build environment `pkgs.stdenv` with all the "
"dependencies present to compile on the build platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:153
msgid ""
"Apply the appropriate host platform configuration to all the packages in "
"`pkgsCross`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:155
msgid ""
"Taking `pkgs.pkgsCross.<host>.hello` will produce the package `hello` "
"compiled on the build platform to run on the `<host>` platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:157
msgid ""
"There are multiple equivalent ways to access packages targeted to the host "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:159
msgid ""
"Explicitly pick the host platform package from within the build platform "
"environment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:161
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"release-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs {};\n"
"in\n"
"pkgs.pkgsCross.aarch64-multiplatform.hello\n"
msgstr ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"release-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs {};\n"
"in\n"
"pkgs.pkgsCross.aarch64-multiplatform.hello\n"

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:169
msgid ""
"Pass the host platform to `crossSystem` when importing `nixpkgs`. This "
"configures `nixpkgs` such that all its packages are built for the host "
"platform:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:172
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"release-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs { crossSystem = { config = \"aarch64-unknown-linux-"
"gnu\"; }; };\n"
"in\n"
"pkgs.hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:180
msgid ""
"Equivalently, you can pass the host platform as an argument to `nix-build`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/cross-compilation.md:182
msgid ""
"$ nix-build '<nixpkgs>' -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-23.11 \\\n"
"  --arg crossSystem '{ config = \"aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\"; }' \\\n"
"  -A hello\n"
msgstr ""
"$ nix-build '<nixpkgs>' -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-23.11 \\\n"
"  --arg crossSystem '{ config = \"aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\"; }' \\\n"
"  -A hello\n"

